ACT:
 U.P. Khandsari Sugar (Levy) order 1981: Levy order- Validity of Khandsari manufacturers required to surrender 50% of production-Fixation of price for levy khandsari sugar-Whether valid-Whether colourable exercise of power.
 The U.P. Khandsari Sugar (Levy) order, 1981 issued in exercise of powers under section 3 of the Essential Commodities Act, 1955, required Khandsari manufacturing units to surrender levy of 50% of the production by sulphitation units in the first process. The balance 50% with the total production by subsequent process was left free to be sold in the open market by the manufacturing units. The price fixed for the levy Khandsari sugar was Rs.
 320 per quintal.
 
